text:
its great in almost every regard but I have to admit when playing it for the first time recently a glaring downside that stuck out and kinda dampened the experience for me was the enemy encounters, theres not really any proper parts in the game where you actually have to evade and progress with an enemy in the area searching for you (except maybe the room with all the pipes where youre searching for the orb shards), most of the time an enemy will spawn with a sound and you hide and then once youve hidden they despawn and theres zero threat and you can continue walking around normally

would've been a pretty 10/10 game if they just didnt have the enemies despawn and you actually had a more alien isolation type experience, its maybe not what frictional wanted to do with amnesia but it makes for a more thoroughly scary experience and its something they seemed to do a lot better in Soma
